gomodel:SYNGO_5168  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: Figure 1: DAGL-α (DAGLA) antibody specificity validation using knockout mice.\n\nFigure 3: immunogold EM imaging of the ventromedial nucleus of the hypothalamus showed DAGL-α (DAGLA) particles at the membranes of dendrites and dendritic spines. 54.4 % of dendrites and 44.4 % of dendritic spines were DAGL-α immunopositive.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Six wild-type C57BL/6 N female mice (3-5 month old) were used in this study.\"\n\nantibody:\nDAGL-α (2 μg/ml, made in rabbit, Frontier Science co. Ltd, Shinko-nishi, Ishikari, Hokkaido, Japan)\n\n\"Specificity of the DAGL-α antibody was assessed in hypothalamus of DAGL-α knock-out mice processed for this method.\n...\nThe specificity of the DAGL-α antibody has also been confirmed in previous studies (Yoshida et al. 2006; Uchigashima et al. 2007; Puente et al. 2011).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5168" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

